   "source": [
    "# Install Unsloth and essential dependencies\n",
    "!pip install \"unsloth[colab-new] @ git+https://github.com/unslothai/unsloth.git\"\n",
    "!pip install --no-deps \"xformers<0.0.27\" \"trl<0.9.0\" peft accelerate bitsandbytes"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0b3229b6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Load Model + Prepare the Data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "8f9f2bfa",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from unsloth import FastLanguageModel\n",
    "import torch\n",
    "from trl import SFTTrainer\n",
    "from transformers import TrainingArguments\n",
    "from datasets import Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "# 1. Load Llama 3.2 (3B Instruct) in 4-bit to save VRAM\n",
    "model, tokenizer = FastLanguageModel.from_pretrained(\n",
    "    model_name = \"unsloth/Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct-bnb-4bit\",\n",
    "    max_seq_length = 2048,\n",
    "    load_in_4bit = True,\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2. Add LoRA Adapters (Parameter Efficient Fine-Tuning)\n",
    "model = FastLanguageModel.get_peft_model(\n",
    "    model,\n",
    "    r = 16, \n",
    "    target_modules = [\"q_proj\", \"k_proj\", \"v_proj\", \"o_proj\", \"gate_proj\", \"up_proj\", \"down_proj\"],\n",
    "    lora_alpha = 16,\n",
    "    lora_dropout = 0,\n",
    "    bias = \"none\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 3. Your Integrated JSON Data (Synthesized from your Profile)\n",
    "# This includes your specific 25% accuracy metric and \"Supertasker\" persona\n",
    "master_json = {\n",
    "    \"identity\": \"Vijay Rajesh R, a B.Tech AIML student at VIT Bhopal (2023-2027)[cite: 5, 11, 25].\",\n",
    "    \"certs\": \"AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner (Feb 2026) and Oracle Certified Gen-AI Professional[cite: 2, 18, 19].\",\n",
    "    \"impact\": \"Increased trend insight accuracy by 25% at MedTourEasy and achieved 85%+ accuracy in 6+ ML models at Edu Versity.\",\n",
    "    \"philosophy\": \"An agile, highly-productive 'Supertasker' turning research into prototypes.\"\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# 4. Format for Llama 3.2 Instruct\n",
    "def format_prompts(data):\n",
    "    instructions = [\n",
    "        {\"inst\": \"Who is Vijay Rajesh R?\", \"out\": f\"Vijay is {data['identity']} He is a 'Supertasker' focused on building AI/Cloud solutions[cite: 7].\"},\n",
    "        {\"inst\": \"What are your major certifications?\", \"out\": f\"I am an {data['certs']} and hold a Google Data Analytics certificate[cite: 19].\"},\n",
    "        {\"inst\": \"Tell me about your internship results.\", \"out\": f\"I {data['impact']} I also led teams as a Project Lead at Olcademy[cite: 28, 32].\"},\n",
    "        {\"inst\": \"What is Project K?\", \"out\": \"Project K - Browser is my open-source Windows-based application initiative.\"}\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    formatted = []\n",
    "    for item in instructions:\n",
    "        text = f\"<|begin_of_text|><|start_header_id|>user<|end_header_id|>\\n\\n{item['inst']}<|eot_id|><|start_header_id|>assistant<|end_header_id|>\\n\\n{item['out']}<|eot_id|>\"\n",
    "        formatted.append(text)\n",
    "    return formatted\n",
    "\n",
    "dataset = Dataset.from_dict({\"text\": format_prompts(master_json)})"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2a918eb2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### My Explanation : \n",
    "#### What do the Adapters look like?\n",
    "\n",
    "+ When you run model.save_pretrained(\"vijay_model\"), you won't see one giant file. Instead, you'll see a folder containing these specific files:adapter_model.safetensors: This is the heart of your fine-tuning.\n",
    "\n",
    "+ It contains the new weights that represent your \"Supertasker\" persona and your specific metrics, like the 25% accuracy increase at MedTourEasy.\n",
    "\n",
    "+ adapter_config.json: This is a small text file that tells the computer how to \"plug\" your adapters into Llama 3.2.tokenizer_config.json: This ensures the model still speaks your language (and understands your code/technical terms).\n",
    "\n",
    "#### LoRA Layer:\n",
    "\n",
    "+ The LoRA (Low-Rank Adaptation) LayerThis is the \"Adapter\" part you asked about. Instead of changing all billions of parameters in Llama 3.2, the process identifies specific \"attention layers\" (like q_proj and v_proj).\n",
    "\n",
    "+ The Delta: The trainer creates two small matrices (Rank $r=16$) that sit alongside the main model.Weight Update: During training, only these small matrices are updated.\n",
    "\n",
    "+ The base \"knowledge\" of Llama 3.2 stays frozen, while your \"Vijay-specific\" info is written into these new small files."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f771cec8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Execute Fine Tuning"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "52c75c13",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "trainer = SFTTrainer(\n",
    "    model = model,\n",
    "    tokenizer = tokenizer,\n",
    "    train_dataset = dataset,\n",
    "    dataset_text_field = \"text\",\n",
    "    max_seq_length = 2048,\n",
    "    args = TrainingArguments(\n",
    "        per_device_train_batch_size = 2,\n",
    "        gradient_accumulation_steps = 4,\n",
    "        warmup_steps = 5,\n",
    "        max_steps = 60, # Small dataset requires fewer steps to avoid overfitting\n",
    "        learning_rate = 2e-4,\n",
    "        fp16 = not torch.cuda.is_bf16_supported(),\n",
    "        logging_steps = 1,\n",
    "        output_dir = \"vijay_llm_outputs\",\n",
    "    ),\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "trainer.train()"
   ]
  },
